Millions have been displaced, here at home and beyond. We account for some 30% of the entire asylum population of the world. Today, the Northerners who descended on us the same anarchy, robberies, death sentence and fundamentalist terrorism find themselves discombobulated. What they are seeing as a major soft drink brand, and the many hundreds of brands it advertises are also in Cameroon. On the other side, we have benefited from the Airtel-Tigo combination and the millions of money that stays in Cameroon at a time when Corona is grappling the world.

Yaounde In Front

The court may not have spoken yet, but it seems we are in the final lap with the liquidation of MTN-Cameroon, the entity formed in 2000 when MTN bought the 49% it did not have in Cameroon to increase the holding to 100%. The merger of MTN Nigeria and Celtel gave birth to Celtel Nigeria as MTN-MTN was known, after the Nigerian competition authorities forced the merger upon the two companies on the grounds that Airtel-Vodafone was diminishing competition in that market.
